INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(227, 1, '2012-09-06 10:15:21', '2012-09-06 17:15:21', 'The UCLA Events Office assists film companies, photographers and other media representatives with requests to film on campus. Requests for news reporting should be directed to the <a href="http://newsroom.ucla.edu/portal/ucla/default.aspx" target="_blank">UCLA Office of Media Relations</a>.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How to Film at UCLA [link to section below on new page]</li>\r\n	<li>Client and film list [link to section below on new page]</li>\r\n	<li>Film Locations Gallery [pull content from here: <a href="http://www.events.ucla.edu/portal/locations/">http://www.events.ucla.edu/portal/locations/</a>]</li>\r\n	<li>Student Filming [link to section below on new page]</li>\r\n	<li>Filming FAQs [link to section below on new page]</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span id="how"> </span>\r\n<h2>How to Film at UCLA</h2>\r\nThe following guidelines were established to provide you with an outstanding film or photography experience at UCLA and to assure that University business can proceed without interruption.\r\nDownload a full PDF copy of GUIDELINES FOR MOTION PICTURE/VIDEO/FILM or PHOTOGRAPHY of the UCLA CAMPUS [add link]\r\nSteps to a Successful Film or Photography Shoot\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Review the UCLA Film and Photography Guidelines above.</li>\r\n	<li>Contact the UCLA Events Office to schedule a scout and select an appropriate location and date with your UCLA Location Manager. [LINK TO CONTACT PAGE]</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain a cost estimate from your UCLA Location Manager and sign your contract.</li>\r\n	<li>During your shoot, direct all inquiries and questions to your on-site UCLA Location Manager.</li>\r\n	<li>After your shoot, you will receive a final invoice within 10-30 days.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a class="alignright" href="#top">back to top ↑</a>\r\n\r\n<span id="client"> </span>\r\n<h2>Client and film list</h2>\r\nThe UCLA Events Office is the University''s coordinating unit for all location shooting such as feature films, commercials, stills and other media. Our client list represents the best in Hollywood.\r\nPast Clients:\r\n<div class="fourCol nomargin">Dreamworks\r\nWarner Bros\r\nColumbia Pictures\r\nHBO\r\nESPN\r\nBBC\r\nCBS Productions\r\nNBC Studios\r\nNickelodeon\r\nFood Network\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="fourCol nomargin">\r\n20th Century Fox TV\r\nHonda\r\nToyota\r\nGQ\r\nWells Fargo\r\nTarget\r\nNordstrom\r\nAdidas\r\nSony Music\r\nYahoo!\r\n</div>\r\n<a class="alignright" href="#top">back to top ↑</a>\r\n\r\n<div class="clearer"></div>\r\n<span id="student"> </span>\r\n\r\n<h2>Student Filming</h2>\r\nRegistered UCLA students may apply for a film permit at no charge provided the filming is related to academic work for the School of Theater, Film &amp; Television, University Extension, Student Media or the Office of Residential Life TV. Certain UCLA students taking a required class and not part of the above departments may still be qualify for a fee waived film permit. A film warrant [add link to PDF] and location confirmation is required to process a film permit. Please contact the UCLA Events Office for more information.\r\n\r\nNon-UCLA film students are subject to the same rules and regulations that apply to commercial film shoots [link to How to Film at UCLA]. UCLA does not waive any campus location or service fees for non-UCLA film students; however, the film permit fee is reduced.\r\nAll UCLA and non-UCLA students must review the following Student Film Shoot Guidelines:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="#">Student Film Shoot Guidelines</a> (PDF)</li>\r\n	<li><a href="#">Student Film Location Form</a> (PDF)</li>\r\n	<li><a href="#">Student Film Warrant</a> (PDF)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a class="alignright" href="#top">back to top ↑</a>\r\n\r\n<span id="faq"> </span>\r\n<h2>Filming FAQs</h2>\r\n<p><strong>How much notice can I give before scouting?</strong>\r\nPlease email or call the UCLA Events Office to schedule a scout. Depending on the number of locations, we will need between two to five working days to schedule a scout.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Where can I film?</strong>\r\nFilming is allowed in most quads, some exteriors of buildings, some classrooms, hallways, auditoriums, sidewalks and streets. Locations will be approved on a case-by-case basis and is contingent on the academic calendar and availability.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What areas are restricted?</strong>\r\nFilming is not allowed at the following locations: the UCLA Medical Center, medical offices, labs, dorm rooms, private offices, dining halls, Murphy Hall, Chancellor’s Residence, full façade of Royce Hall, full façade of Powell Library, full façade of Kerckhoff Hall and the Bruin Bear.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Do I need script approval from the University?</strong>\r\nYes. A film permit cannot be issued without script approval from the University. A script or storyboard must be submitted in advance for consideration.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What if I have a parking citation while filming there?</strong>\r\nAll parking citations received during filming will not be rescinded by the University. Please follow normal procedures to contest all parking citations. The instructions on how to contest are written on the back of the citation.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Can I bring my own caterer?</strong>\r\nThe production company is allowed to bring in its own caterer to most locations on campus.</p>\r\n<p><strong>I am making a low budget feature. Is there a discount?</strong>\r\nWhile we agree that your film project is important, UCLA is non-profit and as such cannot discount any rates.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Can I film stock footage of the campus?</strong>\r\nNo. Stock footage of the campus is prohibited.</p>\r\n\r\n<a class="alignright" href="#top">back to top ↑</a>', 'Filming and Photography', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-32', '', '', '2012-09-06 10:15:21', '2012-09-06 17:15:21', '', 9, 'http://uclaevents.com/development/ucla-events/9-revision-32/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
